metadata.description:
"Gestalt" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at The Ever-Evolving World of Art, Art Basel Hong-Kong, 2022

A flurry of many elements derived from my past (and future) strewn across a single canvas. As random as things seem, collectively time tends to reveal hints of order in the chaos. Sometimes, more is more.

metadata.name: Grove #94
metadata.description:
A generative, impressionist painting of a small grove of trees in one of the four seasons. In spring and summer, flowers bloom in the meadow. A rare variation will create a charcoal drawing on white or black paper. Super rare will create a lighted winter scene that may have a moon behind the tree.

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.

Press 's' to save a screenshot at any point. Image size is 1400x1082px.

Add '&size=#' to the end of the live view URL to render a variation of your edition at a resolution from 300 to 3,000 px.

On the paintings only, adding '&bg=true' will stop the painting after the background. Adding '&size=3000&bg=true' will give you a nice desktop background! 

Common Features:
- About 12-14 trees
- One of the four seasons
- One of 12 highlight color tints
- One of 12 shadow color tints
- Varying levels of distance haze
- Varying max brush sizes
- Varying amount of colors in the strokes

Less Common
- 15% chance of a charcoal drawing
- 50% chance it to be a dark winter scene

Rare
- Winter drawing with lights on the tree

Super Rare
- Winter drawing with a moon behind the tree

metadata.name: Averno #40
metadata.description:
The work sits at the intersection of atmospheric abstraction and symbolic representation,
where generative aesthetics become a vehicle for an exploration of the perceptual threshold between form and dissolution.
Vertical structures, resembling slender shrubs or nervous filaments, construct a visual lattice that oscillates between transparency and density, suggesting a synthetic vegetation suspended between nature and algorithm.

The composition stands out for its use of digital color, with gradients that simulate traditional techniques such as pastel or watercolor, while maintaining a coherence typical of code. The generative intervention is not merely ornamental: it is a formal strategy that translates the indeterminacy of the landscape into an autonomous aesthetic language.

The sinuous shapes that emerge from below and rise upwards are not mere presences: they suggest a humanity in the making‚Äîor rather, an anthropomorphic echo generated by the system, a tension between organic mark-making and computational logic.

metadata.name: Imi #152
metadata.description:
Recursive subdivision based on "returns", inspired by Imi Knoebel. (German painter and sculptor known for his contributions to and shaping of 20th century Minimalist abstract art.)

Click for new composition, doubleclick for fullscreen. Press s to save a printable SVG file.

metadata.name: Reading a book #655
metadata.description:
The formal structure of a book is beautiful by itself, but its aesthetic is the tacit atmosphere within which events take place in a story.

The WebGL real-time animation sets up an initial grid based on the fxhash. The grid cells get subdivided into another grid and the resulting cells become filled with pixels in color (~33%) or black and white (~66%).
The colored pixels come in 3 different coloring styles.
- Big Palette (~49%)
- Small Palette (~49%)
- Monochrome [b/w] (~2%)
4 noise algorithms modify the pixels of selected grid cells while at the same time 4 reset algorithms reassemble the initial image. The selected cells switch over time.

metadata.description:
In the absence of sound, the wavy lines traced the path of silence;
and the circles, gently, like thoughts emerging from stillness, rose and fell.
When I Was Quiet is a story of moments remembered only through their image.

metadata.name: Tenebris #4
metadata.description:
Something stirs from the depths of shadow, not light, not darkness, but the breath between. Is there light within darkness? Or is darkness itself the meaning?

A study in silence and contrast. Where emptiness becomes form, and light exists only as the edge of shadow. "Tenebris" is not darkness itself, but the breath that lingers between presence and absence.

metadata.name: SENTINELS #1
metadata.description:
The SENTINELS, with their cold, diamond forms, reign over an unsettling realm. Their presence exudes an aura of solemn guardianship, shrouded with unease. These are not friendly guides; they are silent arbiters of the unknown, both protectors and judges of the enigma that is their terrain. As you gaze into their world, let these haunting apparitions remind you of the vastness of the cosmos. 

The SENTINELS beckon you to explore the sinister beauty of the abyss, to question, and to wander through a digital realm where the eerie and the captivating coexist.

Paranoia is a necessary skill whenever a SENTINEL is involved.
 
SENTINELS is not only an exploration of the sublime-it also empowers collectors to generate physical artifacts from the void. With a keystroke, you choose your format:

Press ‚Äòs‚Äô or ‚Äò1‚Äô to save a compact version
‚Äò2‚Äô for a print-ready image
‚Äò3‚Äô for a high-resolution image
